comment: Correctly called OOB, last touched by Indiana.
Monroe (DET) sets the screen on Hill (IND) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Jackson (DET) holds Hill (IND) and restricts his FOM as he attempts to catch the entry pass.
Monroe (DET) sets the screen on West (IND) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
West (IND) makes contact with Caldwell-Pope's (DET) body on the jump shot.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Caldwell-Pope (DET) was attempting a 3 pointer when he was fouled by West (IND) was upheld.
Hill (IND) does not go through the defending Lucas III's (DET) space and the contact by Lucas III affects Hill's movement toward the basket.
